--------------------------------------------------
8. Feature Development Workflow (TDD)
--------------------------------------------------

All features must be implemented using Test-Driven Development.
Writing implementation code before tests is not allowed.

Step 1: Clarify requirements and acceptance criteria
Step 2: Update technical specification if necessary
Step 3: Write failing tests first (RED)
  - Write tests based on acceptance criteria
  - Run tests and confirm they FAIL
  - A passing test before implementation means the test is invalid
Step 4: Write minimal implementation (GREEN)
  - Write only enough code to make the tests pass
  - Run tests and confirm they PASS
Step 5: Refactor (REFACTOR)
  - Clean up code structure and readability
  - Do not change behavior
  - Run tests and confirm they still PASS
Step 6: Update documentation

Repeat steps 3-5 for each unit of functionality.
Target test coverage: >= 80%


--------------------------------------------------
9. Testing
--------------------------------------------------

All code must have tests written BEFORE implementation (TDD).

Tests must be placed in:

tests/

Examples:

tests/api_tests/
tests/ai_tests/

Bug fixes must also follow TDD:
1. Write a failing test that reproduces the bug (RED)
2. Fix the bug with minimal changes (GREEN)
3. Refactor if needed, keep tests green


--------------------------------------------------
10. Scripts
--------------------------------------------------

Automation scripts must be stored in:

scripts/

Examples:

scripts/run_eval.sh
scripts/build_index.sh


--------------------------------------------------
11. AI Capability Levels
--------------------------------------------------

Projects may include the following AI capability levels:

none
prompt-workflow
rag
agent-system

Agents must generate the appropriate architecture
based on the selected capability.


--------------------------------------------------
12. Code Quality
--------------------------------------------------

Agents must follow these rules:

- Write modular code
- Avoid large monolithic files
- Prefer clear function boundaries
- Use descriptive variable names
- Include comments when logic is complex


--------------------------------------------------
13. Documentation Updates
--------------------------------------------------

When a feature is added or changed:

Agents must update the relevant documentation:

docs/spec.md
docs/api.md
docs/architecture.md


